- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on Fully Homomorphic Encryption (FHE) which is a groundbreaking invention in cryptography. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper presents a novel hardware architecture for FHE. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses techniques to reduce on-chip memory consumption. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss programming languages used in the implementation of the hardware architecture. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but possible as the paper may discuss the system-level design of the hardware architecture.
